    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1979-04-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1979-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="165"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d165">
                <head>165. Memorandum From Acting Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_CWM_1"
                        >Christopher</persName> to President <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1"
                        >Carter</persName>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d165fn1">Source: Carter Library, National
                        Security Affairs, Brzezinski Material, Subject File, Box 21, Evening Reports
                        (State) 4/79. Secret. <persName corresp="#p_CJE_1">Carter</persName>
                        initialed the memorandum.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1979-04-07">April 7, 1979</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">Uganda</hi>. We told the Executive Committee of the Uganda
                    National Liberation Front, in response to their inquiry, that once a new
                    government is in place, we would look forward to restoring relations and
                    reopening our Embassy. We said we would want to work closely with a new
                    government which had the support of the Ugandan people and was able to gain
                    wider African acceptance, in the expectation that it would move soon to
                    reestablish democratic institutions. Looking ahead, we said we would entertain
                    requests from such a government for humanitarian assistance and longer-term
                    development aid, and also work with the Congress to remove restrictions on trade
                    with Uganda.<note n="2" xml:id="d165fn2">In telegram 1502 from USUN, April 6,
                        the Mission reported on the April 3 meeting with <gloss target="#t_UNLF_1"
                            >UNLF</gloss> representatives. (National Archives, RG 59, Central
                        Foreign Policy File, P790158–0240)</note>
                </p>
                <p>[Omitted here are items unrelated to East Africa.]</p>
            </div>
        </body>
